data.title: WWE, ECW, NWA legends in Pawcatuck, Ct for a Cause

data.text:
(Reporter)

Paul Gabriel is a Blues Music Award nominated guitarist, singer and songwriter. In March 2018 Paul Gabriel was presented with the Lifetime Achievement Award from the Connecticut Blues Society for excellence in guitar playing, singing and songwriting; also for outstanding bandleader and entertainer. In July 2018 he was inducted into the CT Blues Hall Of Fame as a Master Blues Artist, in 2020 he was inducted into the New England Music Hall Of Fame for his musical contributions to the music business over fifty year's. New England's first triple crown hall of famer. Websitehttps://www.paulgabriel.net/

(Columnist)

Evan Ginzburg is a published author and was an Associate Producer on the Oscar-nominated movie The Wrestler and acclaimed documentary 350 Days. He is a 30-plus-year film, radio, and TV veteran, has been an NYC club booker, and is a voice-over actor on the radiodrama Kings of the Ring. In addition, he is the Senior Editor for Pro Wrestling Stories. Read his blog at www.evanginzburg.com. He can be reached on Twitter @evan_ginzburg, or by e-mail at evan_ginzburg@yahoo.com.

Marie Parente of Cranston, RI, is a wife and mother of two beautiful children. She married her best friend, Michael Parente. Shehas been employed for the past nine years by a well-known insurance defense firm, Higgins, Cavanagh & Cooney, LLP,and has been a certified paralegal for 20 years. She has modeled intermittently for 18 years and had a lead role in a television commercial. She has been on three billboards in New York City for Supermodels Unlimited. She enjoysspending time with her family and friends, cooking, dancing, bird watching, and working out.Motivated by motherhood, Marie is an advocate for childhood hunger awareness, a worthwhile cause affecting many families in the United States. Today, 1 in 6 children in America are at risk of suffering from food insecurity, and Marie is passionate about connecting these vulnerable children throughout the country with the nutritious food they need to grow and thrive. Through her connection with the non-profit organization ‚ÄúNo Kid Hungry,‚Äù which ensures children have access to food where they live, learn, and play, Marie has worked tirelessly over the past several years to help raise more than 50,000 meals. She has the backing and support of her family and her extensive personal and professional network, Marie will raise funds, educate on the topic of hunger through her writing and public appearances, and champion for the children nationwide who cannot afford a meal. Her overriding goal is to end childhood hunger and to break any stigmas associated with their suffering.

Chelsea is an American transgender actress born Feb 6 1982 in Maryland. She grew up in Texas, spent some years overseas in Japan with military parents and later went to college in New England for Electrical Engineering. During this time, she was also an avid cosplayer at local comicon conventions. After working in the engineering field for 13 years in New Hampshire, she decided to follow her passion and turn her cosplay/modeling hobby into an acting career.
